                p Inspiration is flowing. I've always been fascinated with space and site. Space is my area of expertise. Building a space allows the viewers to directly enter an experience. However, a site is wider. The amplitude of the sound can vibrate the body directly, directly enter the heart, and bring to mind imaginary pictures. Sounds create sights, forming superimposed spaces. Body performance lets us skip the brain, allow us to engage with ancient flow and expression. These are the possibilities I want to pursue now. As a result, I started "The Wind Brings Mother's Voice" art project in 2020, and the project has continued since then.
